m, BlinkMacSystemFont, \'Segoe UI\', \'Helvetica Neue\', Arial, sans-serif;\">The Huawei Y9 (2019) runs Android 8 and is powered by a 4,000mAh battery.</p>\r\n<p><br style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #282828; font-family: Roboto, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \'Segoe UI\', \'Helvetica Neue\', Arial, sans-serif;\" /><br style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #282828; font-family: Roboto, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \'Segoe UI\', \'Helvetica Neue\', Arial, sans-serif;\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 8px 0px; margin: 0px; color: #282828; font-family: Roboto, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \'Segoe UI\', \'Helvetica Neue\', Arial, sans-serif;\">As far as the cameras are concerned, the Huawei Y9 (2019) on the rear packs a 2 &amp; 13-megapixel camera with an f/1.8 aperture. The rear camera setup has autofocus. It sports a 2 &amp; 16-megapixel camera on the front for selfies.</p>\r\n<p><br style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #282828; font-family: Roboto, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \'Segoe UI\', \'Helvetica Neue\', Arial, sans-serif;\" /><br style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #282828; font-family: Roboto, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \'Segoe UI\', \'Helvetica Neue\', Arial, sans-serif;\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 8px 0px; margin: 0px; color: #282828; font-family: Roboto, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \'Segoe UI\', \'Helvetica Neue\', Arial, sans-serif;\">The Huawei Y9 (2019) runs EMUI 8.2&nbsp;based on Android 8&nbsp;and packs 64GB of inbuilt storage that can be expanded via microSD card (up to 512GB). The Huawei Y9 (2019) is a dual-SIM (GSM and GSM) smartphone.</p>\r\n<p><br style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #282828; font-family: Roboto, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \'Segoe UI\', \'Helvetica Neue\', Arial, sans-serif;\" /><br style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #282828; font-family: Roboto, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \'Segoe UI\', \'Helvetica Neue\', Aria