ka_NG_logo?adId=logo&amp;creativeASIN=logo&amp;linkId=eeeb808716928fde52df04c9ffeda48a&amp;tag=naijatechguide-20&amp;linkCode=w41&amp;ref-refURL=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.naijatechguide.com%2F2019%2F10%2Finfinix-s5.html&amp;slotNum=0&amp;imprToken=XweMq0I6iQ7NCBTMLjlR.g&amp;adType=smart&amp;adMode=auto&amp;adFormat=grid&amp;impressionTimestamp=1574030458374&amp;ac-ms-src=nsa-ads&amp;cid=nsa-ads\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Ads by Amazon</a><span style=\"color: #282828; font-family: Roboto, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \'Segoe UI\', \'Helvetica Neue\', Arial, sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 8px 0px; margin: 0px 0px 24px; overflow-wrap: break-word; font-family: Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif; line-height: 24px; color: #222222;\">Design-wise, there isn&rsquo;t much to say about comparison, when you compare the Infinix Hot S5 to its predecessor the&nbsp;<a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; background: 0px 0px; display: inline-block; color: #4db2ec; font-weight: bold; text-decoration-line: none !important;\" href=\"https://www.naijatechguide.com/2019/04/infinix-hot-s4.html\">Infinix Hot S4</a>, as both do not actually look alike. The Infinix Hot S5 features a fresh design.</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 8px 0px; margin: 0px 0px 24px; overflow-wrap: break-word; font-family: Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif; line-height: 24px; color: #222222;\">The smartphone features a plastic build. There is plastic on the rear as well as on the frame. On the rear of this device, there is a camera module, a camera flash, a fingerprint sensor, and the Infinix branding.</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 8px 0px; margin: 0px 0px 24px; overflow-wrap: break-word; font-family: Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif; line-height: 24px; color: #222222;\">Flip the Infinix S5 to get a front view, we are presented with its star feature, which is a 6.6-inch hole-punch IPS LCD display, with a screen resolution of 720 x 1600 and a screen density of 266 PPI. Although the top bezel has been shrunk to the barest minimum, there is still a noticeable amount of bezel below the display.</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 8px 0px; margin: 0px 0px 24px; overflow-wrap: break-word; font-family: Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif; line-height: 24px; color: #222222;\">For color variants, the Infinix Hot S5 comes in Quetzal Cyan, Violet, Nebula Black. This means that if you are to purchase the smartphone, you would have the option of having a smartphone with any of these three colors.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 8px 0px; margin: 0px; font-weight: 400; color: #282828; font-family: Roboto, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \'Segoe UI\', \'Helvetica Neue\', Arial, sans-serif;\">The Cameras</h2>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 8px 0px; margin: 0px 0px 24px; overflow-wrap: break-word; font-family: Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif; line-height: 24px; color: #222222;\">The Infinix S5 packs in impressive camera hardware. The camera hardware on this device may not appear to be stellar in the midst of other top smartphones, but the affordable nature of this smartphone makes these cameras stellar for the price.</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 8px 0px; margin: 0px 0px 24px; overflow-wrap: break-word; font-family: Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif; line-height: 24px; color: #222222;\">Unlike its predecessor, the Infinix S5 comes packed with a quad-camera system on the rear. This Quad camera system on the rear is home to 16MP primary camera with an aperture of F/1.8, a 5MP ultra-wide camera, a 2MP depth sensor, and a 2MP macro lens.</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 8px 0px; margin: 0px 0px 24px; overflow-wrap: break-word; font-family: Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif; line-height: 24px; color: #222222;\">With this rear camera setup, you would be able to take photos in HDR, Panorama mode, shoot 1080p videos with frame rates maxed at 30fps and do lots more.</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 8px 0px; margin: 0px 0px 24px; overflow-wrap: break-word; font-family: Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif; line-height: 24px; color: #222222;\">Upfront, the Infinix S5 features a 32MP selfies camera. Due t the fact that there isn&rsquo;t enough space for a selfie flash, the Infinix Hot S5 relies on extreme screen brightness to light up photos taken in the dark.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 8px 0px; margin: 0px; font-weight: 400; color: #282828; font-family: Roboto, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \'Segoe UI\', \'Helvetica Neue\', Arial, sans-serif;\">Hardware and Software</h2>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 8px 0px; margin: 0px 0px 24px; overflow-wrap: break-word; font-family: Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif; line-height: 24px; color: #222222;\">The hardware can be best described as standard. Hardware specs setup here is kind of what you will use to describe a smartphone that can perform a lot of more than basic tasks, without glitches.</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 8px 0px; margin: 0px 0px 24px; overflow-wrap: break-word; font-family: Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif; line-height: 24px; color: #222222;\">The Infinix Hot S5 features an Octa-core Mediatek MT6761 Helio P22 processor clocked at 2.0 GHz.</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 8px 0px; margin: 0px 0px 24px; overflow-wrap: break-word; font-family: Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif; line-height: 24px; color: #222222;\">It also features a 6GB RAM with option of 64GB or 128GB of internal storage. Need more memory? The phone supports up to 256GB for Micro-SD expansion.</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 8px 0px; margin: 0px 0px 24px; overflow-wrap: break-word; font-family: Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif; line-height: 24px; color: #222222;\">The cell phone houses a non-removable 4000mAh Li-Po battery. Please note that the S5 doesn&rsquo;t support fast charge.</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 8px 0px; margin: 0px 0px 24px; overflow-wrap: break-word; font-family: Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif; line-height: 24px; color: #222222;\">On the software side, the Infinix S5 runs Infinix&rsquo;s XOS 5.0 on top of the Android 9.0 (Pie) operating system. There was no word on the Android 10 update when this article was written.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 8px 0px; margin: 0px; font-weight: 400; color: #282828; font-family: Roboto, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \'Segoe UI\', \'Helvetica Neue\', Arial, sans-serif;\">Connectivity</h2>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 8px 0px; margin: 0px 0px 24px; overflow-wrap: break-word; font-family: Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif; line-height: 24px; color: #222222;\">The Infinx S5 features a 3.5mm headphone jack, a Micro-USB port (USB 2.0), dual-band Wi-Fi and Bluetooth 5.0.</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 8px 0px; margin: 0px 0px 24px; overflow-wrap: break-word; font-family: Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif; line-height: 24px; color: #222222;\">It has support for 4G connectivity. Please note that 4G LTE bands supported in this device include</p>', 'buy infinix s5 pro', 500, 2000, 1, 10, 'products/March2020/G7wd3G3cxr29uatySx84.jpg', NULL, '2', 1, '2020-03-12 15:07:31', '2020-06-24 09:15:46'),
