(1118, 'Infinix Hot 9 6.6&quot; IPS Display, Android 10.0; 13MP + 2MP + 2MP + QVGA Quad Rear Cameras, 2GB Ram 32GB Rom- Quetzal Cyan', 'Infinix_Hot_9_6.6&quot;_IPS_Display,_Android_10.0;_13MP_+_2MP_+_2MP_+_QVGA_Quad_Rear_Cameras,_2GB_Ram_32GB_Rom-_Quetzal_Cyan', '6.6-inch IPS Display, 720 x 1600 pixels (269 PPI)Octa-core MediaTek Helio A25 (12 nm)Android 10.0; XOS 6.02GB RAM32GB  Built-in Storage, with SD-Card Support13MP + 2MP + 2MP + QVGA Quad Rear Cameras8MP Front CameraFingerprint Sensor (Rear)5000 mAh No...', 48372, 'The Infinx Hot 9 bears features that award it the tag of being a worthy upgrade of the Infinix Hot 8. It features an improved design, processor, cameras and lots more. In this article, we explore the Infinix Hot 9 specs and price, which will help you make your purchase decision.The Design and DisplayThe Infinix Hot 9 features one of the most better-looking design upgrades we have seen in the Hot 9 series. Compare it with that of the Infinix Hot 8 and you immediately notice a very refined design, one that tries it best to fit into the latest trend.The rear of the Infinix Hot 9 features curved edges and a glossy finish with a mild gradation in color. This rear panel is home to a capacitive fingerprint sensor, a quad-camera setup and the Infinix logo, which indicates its an Infinix phone.Upfront, we have set up that resembles that of the Infinix S5. It’s a 6.6-inch IPS LCD display housing a single camera cut-out. This display has a screen resolution of 720 x 1600 pixels and a screen density of 269 PPI.The CamerasInfinix included a beefier camera system in the Hot series this year. They managed to squeeze in quad rear cameras in here, which allowed for more camera features.The primary camera sensor varies according to the storage variants you purchase. variants below 64GB will have a 13MP primary camera, while variants with 64GB and above will have a 16MP primary camera. Other cameras included in this quad-camera setup include a 2MP macro camera, a 2MP depth camera and a QVGA camera which helps in taking photos in low light conditions.This camera setup is supported by a triple LED flash and is capable of shooting photos in HDR, Panorama, and videos maxed at 1080p @ 30fps. for selfies, it makes use of an 8MP shooter, which is capable of shooting photos and also shoot videos maxed at 1080p 30fps.Hardware and SoftwareThe Infinix Hot 9 follows suit with its predecessor. It doesn’t deviate from the category other smartphones in Hot series featured. Performance-wise, you have got a smartphone that isn’t capable of tackling power-intensive tasks.Inside this Android phone is an Octa-core Mediatek MT6762 Helio P22 processor, a PowerVR GE8320 graphics processing unit and a non-removable 5000mAh battery.On the software side, the Infinix Hot 9 runs the XOS 6.0 interface on top of the Android 10.0 operating system.ConnectivityThe Infinix Hot 9 features a 3.5mm headphone jack, a version 2.0 Micro-USB port, dual-band wifi, Bluetooth 5.0.Internet connectivity on the Infinix Hot 9 is capped at 4G LTE. which means downloads and streaming will be capped at 4G speeds.', 'buy Infinix Hot 9 6.6&quot; IPS Display, Android 10.0; 13MP + 2MP + 2MP + QVGA Quad Rear Cameras, 2GB Ram 32GB Rom- Quetzal Cyan online', 500, 5560, 1, 10, 'robot/image1593972528.jpg', NULL, '2', 0, '2020-07-05 22:08:48', '2020-07-05 22:08:48'),
