ing with. For capturing wide-angle photos you have the 8MP ultrawide lens. Taking a wide-angle photo using a normal camera lens is quite difficult. You may be required to move back to capture the whole scene not taking into consideration challenges arising where moving back may be difficult if you\'re in a small tight space. With the ultrawide lens, you no longer need to move back to capture wide scenes. Simply switch to the ultrawide wide mode where the whole scene is captured. The 5MP macro camera is for taking close-up images of small objects. When you try using the main camera to take images of small objects, the images are usually blurry and very poor. With the macro camera, you can get close to your subject without the image without losing focus or clarity. When taking portrait images, you will be using the depth camera. The depth camera blurs out the background around the subject so that all the focus is on the subject. This makes the subject  since they are no distractions pulling focus from the subject. Powerful Processor.With our smartphones being part of our daily lives, they must be able to handle what we require of them promptly without any issues. It can be frustrating to have a smartphone that anytime you run multiple apps at the same time the phone becomes slow and may even stop responding depending on the apps. A powerful processor is therefore important if you don\'t want to get frustrated by your smartphone. With a powerful processor, you can multitask without any loss of speed.Redmi Note 9 Pro which replaces Redmi Note 8 Pro comes with an improved processor that is almost twice as powerful as Redmi Note 8 Pro. The Octa-core Qualcomm Snapdragon 720G processor clocks at 2.3GHz at full throttle. The processor comes with a 36% increase in CPU performance, a 14% increase in GPU performance, and a 115% increase in AI performance. With these improvements, Redmi Note 9 Pro is almost as powerful as some high-end smartphones with the difference being that Redmi Note 9 Pro is a cheap smartphone compared to high-end smartphones. Fast Charging.Big batteries are now a common feature in smartphones. The reason big batteries have become common is that manufacturers have realized that consumers need their smartphone\'s battery power to last the whole day instead of a few hours. Gone are the days of smartphones with small batteries because no one will buy them anymore. Redmi Note 9 Pro comes with a big 5020mAh battery that lasts more than 12 hours on a single charge if you\'re a heavy smartphone user.Since bigger batteries take longer to charge, the problem of charging becomes an issue when you want to use your phone but it takes several hours to charge and you don\'t want to cut the charging since that will spoil your battery. The solution to this is fast charging. Fast charging lets you charge your phone in minutes instead of it taking several hours to become fully charged. Redmi Note 9 Pro comes with 30W Fast Charging that will power up your smartphone quickly so that you are never far from your smartphone. Display Supports 4K Videos.Redmi Note 9 Pro comes with a 6.67\" Dot-in Display. With a Dot-in type of display, you get an uninterrupted cinematic view that lets you enjoy watching your content because they are no ugly notch on the display. Redmi Note 9 Pro display also supports 4K Videos. With 4K starting to be the new normal, you get to jump ahead of the curve and be one among a few people who can watch 4K content on their smartphone. You get to enjoy high-quality cinematic content at the comfort of your own home. Compared to 4K TVs, Redmi Note 9 Pro is a cheap option.', 'buy XIAOMI Redmi Note 9 Pro 6.67-Inch 6GB RAM, 64GB ROM Android 10 (64MP + 8MP + 5MP + 2MP) + 16MP 4G Dual SIM - Tropical Green online', 500, 11000, 1, 10, 'robot/image1593972565.jpg', NULL, '2', 0, '2020-07-05 22:09:25', '2020-07-05 22:09:25'),
